<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - FLYWHEEL REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FLYWHEEL REMOVAL</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The rear oil seal can be serviced in chassis. The procedure is performed as part of engine
                        overhaul and separately, when required.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>IF YOU HAVE A REAR PTO ASSEMBLY, REFER TO REAR PTO SERVICE PROCEDURES FOUND IN THE CHASSIS
                        MANUAL.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Remove the following as follows (F
                <emph type="bold">igure</emph>
                <hotlnk document="e160_166.xml" xrefid="ef1600705">7.5</hotlnk>):
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>REMOVING</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two (2) flywheel mounting bolts located at the 3 and 9 o'clock positions. Install
                    two (2) guide dowel pins
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE4375</emph>
                    at these locations.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove remaining ten (10) flywheel mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide flywheel out of the flywheel housing and off guide dowel pins.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>With flywheel removed, guide dowel pins can be removed from crankshaft flange. Refer to
                            "FLYWHEEL" in this section for further information on inspection and resurfacing.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>FOR APPLICATIONS USING AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSIONS, TAKE NOTE OF POSITION AND ORIENTATION OF
                            FLEXPLATE(S), SPACERS AND RE-INFORCING RING.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
